 {"id":"ft-jehxh","title":"perf(patterns): cache trace pack ids and anchor buckets in detection hot path","description":"Hot path: crates/frankenterm-core/src/patterns.rs:2652-2656 resolves pack_id_for_rule_id() and allocates a String for every candidate rule in detect_with_context_and_trace_inner(); crates/frankenterm-core/src/patterns.rs:2868-2872 also allocates a Vec for every rule that gets an anchor hit. In high-volume capture scans this repeats per detect call even though rule->pack id and anchor bucket cardinality are compile-time properties of EngineIndex.

Concrete optimization: add pack_id (Arc<str> or Box<str>) to CompiledRule during compile_packs, pass borrowed pack_id into trace builders, and pre-size/reuse candidate anchor buckets (SmallVec<[AnchorMatchRef; 2]> or a pooled per-call scratch vec) so common single-anchor rules avoid heap allocation. Add a microbench/proptest fixture over repeated PatternEngine::detect_with_context_and_trace on pattern-rich text to show allocation/count reduction.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"codex-greyfalcon","created_at":"2026-04-27T19:33:17.071291Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T20:03:54.329603Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T20:03:54.329407Z","close_reason":"Cached pattern trace pack IDs and replaced per-hit anchor lookups with prebuilt rule buckets","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"ft-jo7jr","title":"gemini.auth.oauth_required lacks alternate OAuth prompt golden fixtures","description":"Rule: `gemini.auth.oauth_required` in `crates/frankenterm-core/src/patterns.rs:2073` ships three OAuth anchors: `authorize this app`, `complete authentication`, and `sign in with Google`.

Current corpus coverage under `crates/frankenterm-core/tests/corpus/gemini/` has one positive golden pair for the first phrasing and one near-miss pair:
- `oauth_required.txt`
- `oauth_required.expect.json`
- `oauth_required_near_miss.txt`
- `oauth_required_near_miss.expect.json`

There is no committed positive `.txt` + `.expect.json` golden for the other shipped OAuth/browser prompts. Add at least one alternate positive fixture so browser-auth wording drift does not leave this rule effectively single-sample tested.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"pane5","created_at":"2026-04-23T05:52:17.095750Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T06:36:36.433365Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T06:36:36.432202Z","close_reason":"Added 3 alternate golden fixtures under crates/frankenterm-core/tests/corpus/gemini/:
- oauth_required_complete_auth (positive, 'complete authentication' anchor)
- oauth_required_google (positive, 'sign in with Google' anchor)
- oauth_required_ansi_edge (negative — ANSI escape codes injected inside 'authorize this app' break the byte-exact anchor match, mirrors the model_used_ansi_edge shape at gemini/model_used_ansi_edge.txt)

Each positive .expect.json mirrors the existing oauth_required.expect.json schema verbatim (rule_id=gemini.auth.oauth_required, agent_type=gemini, event_type=auth.oauth_required, severity=warning, confidence=0.6, extracted={}) with matched_text swapped for the covered anchor; the ANSI-edge .expect.json is []. Each anchor is taken literally from patterns.rs:2079-2081.

Verification: cargo test -p frankenterm-core --test pattern_corpus corpus_fixtures_match_expected via rch --target /tmp/ft-pane5-jo7jr-target compiled in 8m28s, test ran but aborted at the first pre-existing failure in claude_code/compaction.txt (expected matched_text='compacted 12,345 tokens to 3,210', actual='Auto-compact: context compacted 12,345 tokens to 3,210' — runner order puts claude_code/ before gemini/ so my fixtures are never reached). That failure is orthogonal to this bead; structural schema parity with the already-green oauth_required.{txt,expect.json} pair is the strongest verification available until the compaction-fixture pre-existing blocker lifts.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"ft-jpov5","title":"[ft-y0loj.3] extract frankenterm-core-fleet sub-crate (4 modules)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:53:01.205622Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:28:59.444836Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T04:28:59.444535Z","close_reason":"b88e or successor commit lands a PARTIAL extraction of the fleet sub-crate per the bead's stated SLA. Only fleet_dashboard (35K, zero in-tree importers — true leaf) moved to the new crates/frankenterm-core-fleet/. Initial attempt to move all 4 modules + add a regular dep on the new crate produced an explicit cargo cycle ('cyclic package dependency: package frankenterm-core depends on itself'). The other three fleet modules (fleet_launcher, fleet_memory_controller, fleet_scrollback_coordinator) stay in frankenterm-core because 6 production importers (runtime, unified_telemetry, tx_execution, mission_agent_mail, chaos_scale_harness, ntm_decommission) consume their types substantively (FleetMemoryConfig, FleetMemoryController, CoordinatorTelemetry, PressureSignals, FleetPressureTier, FleetMemorySnapshot, PaneScrollbackInfo). Full extraction blocks on ft-usvnt landing first (extract frankenterm-core-memory: backpressure + memory_budget + memory_pressure as shared-types crate to reverse the dep direction). New sub-crate exists as a workspace member with one module today; lib.rs doc + the parent's lib.rs comment both document the partial cut + the blocker. cargo check --workspace clean via rch on /tmp/ft-cc6-target. cc7 lane (ars/) untouched.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","monolith-split","refactor"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ft-jpov5","depends_on_id":"ft-y0loj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:53:14.345254Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
